        "guide": "<div class='guide-card'><h3>💡 Key facts (so you don’t mess this up)</h3><ul><li><strong>Car:</strong> Mandatory unless you stay in one village only. Public transport is unreliable and slow.</li><li><strong>Island size:</strong> Large → you will drive a lot</li><li><strong>Full loop (with stops):</strong> ~300–400 km for a proper trip</li><li><strong>Strategy:</strong> either 1 base (more driving), or 2 bases (smarter)</li></ul></div><h3>📅 3-DAY ITINERARY (tight but efficient)</h3><p><strong>Where to stay:</strong> Base: Petra or Molyvos (north) - Best combo of scenery + access + vibe</p><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 1 — North highlights (easy start):</strong> Route: Mytilene → Petra → Molyvos (Drive: ~60 km / 1.5h). Land in Mytilene → pick up car. Drive north via coastal route. Stop at Mantamados (monastery) and Skala Sykamnias (tiny fishing village). Afternoon: Petra (church on rock) and Molyvos (castle + sunset). Sleep: Petra / Molyvos.</div><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 2 — Beaches + hot springs:</strong> Driving loop: ~80–100 km. Morning: Eftalou hot springs (quick dip) and North beaches (Anaxos / Petra beach). Midday: Lunch seaside. Afternoon: Explore Molyvos properly (streets, castle). Optional: Chill beach day (don’t overplan).</div><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 3 — Central + departure:</strong> Route: Petra → Kalloni → Mytilene (~70–90 km total). Stop at: Kalloni salt flats (bird area) and Skala Kallonis (lunch). Back to Mytilene: Castle and Harbor walk. Total driving (3 days): ~220–270 km. Very manageable.</div><h3>📅 5-DAY ITINERARY (the correct way to do Lesvos)</h3><p>Now you actually see the island properly.<br><strong>Where to stay (split):</strong> 2 nights: Petra/Molyvos (north) AND 2–3 nights: Skala Eressos OR Plomari (south/west). This reduces stupid backtracking.</p><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 1 — Arrival + north coast:</strong> Same as 3-day Day 1. Mytilene → Petra/Molyvos (~60 km)</div><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 2 — North deep dive:</strong> Molyvos castle + old town. Petra + beach. Eftalou hot springs. Optional hiking / boat trip.</div><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 3 — Cross island (best drive):</strong> Route: North → West (Sigri / Eressos) ~120 km / 2.5–3h. Stops: Kalloni wetlands, Petrified Forest (Sigri – UNESCO geopark). Arrive Skala Eressos (best sunset beach on island). Sleep: Skala Eressos.</div><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 4 — West + south (wild side):</strong> Driving: ~80–120 km. Options: Lazy beach day (Eressos is perfect) OR explore Vatera beach (longest beach), Plomari (ouzo capital), and Mountain village Agiassos.</div><div class='itinerary-step'><strong>Day 5 — Return to Mytilene:</strong> Route: South → Mytilene ~60–90 km. Stops: Olive museum / villages. Mytilene town (castle, food, cafés). Total driving (5 days): ~350–450 km. This is realistic for seeing the island properly.</div><div class='advice-box'><h3>⚠️ Blunt advice (important)</h3><ul><li>Don’t stay only in Mytilene → boring for holidays</li><li>Don’t skip the west (Sigri/Eressos) → it’s the most unique part</li><li>Don’t rely on buses → you’ll regret it within 24h</li><li>Don’t overpack your days → distances look small, roads are slow</li></ul></div><h3>📍 Best areas summarized</h3><ul><li><strong>Molyvos/Petra:</strong> best overall base</li><li><strong>Skala Eressos:</strong> best vibe + beach + chill</li><li><strong>Plomari:</strong> more local, less polished</li><li><strong>Mytilene:</strong> only for arrival/departure</li></ul>"
    },
